[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pianist Tokio Myers crowned BGT winner 2017

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Pianist Tokio Myers has been named the winner of Britain's Got Talent.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He beat off competition from the likes of eight-year-old magician Issy Simpson and comedian Daliso Chaponda to become the winner of the ITV talent show.
Tokio's performance in the final was an emotional version of Rag'n'Bone Man's hit Human, which impressed the judges.
He wins Â£250,000 in prize money and will get to take part at the Royal Variety Performance.
Before appearing on BGT, Tokio had previously supported artists such rapper Kanye West.
